reviews.text: Eat with yout own risk! The taste is good but its kind bit dirty, I smell cat urine coming all over the floor, destroy my appetite

reviews.text: Seems this little place quite famous in Samarinda. They serve soto banjar, sate and even friend rice. Soto banjar in here light, clear soup not heavy like when i ever eat in banjarmasin.
reviews.title: Nice soto banjar in Samarinda

reviews.text: The soup was nice, fried rice also good. They open in the morning, so suitable place to have breakfast or dinner
reviews.title: On my trip, always had dinner in here

reviews.text: I came here just because its rated #2 in tripadvisor. But i dont think that the soto banjar is the best. tasty enough but its just an ordinary soto banjar for me. Yaa, just okay.
reviews.title: Just okay

reviews.text: It is one kind of traditional chicken soup in Indonesia. The taste is rich of  local seasoning such as cinnamon and nutmeg that gives savory sensation.
reviews.title: Must try

reviews.text: I love their soto, so delicious. Their soto is famous in town. Other food serve here is great too such as  kimlo soup and chicken satay.
reviews.title: I love their soto

reviews.text: it's called Soto Banjar, some of Borneo cuisine, Near SCP Mall and Aston Hotel, great taste and price, very strategic location....
reviews.title: Great Taste

reviews.text: the best soto Banjar in Samarinda. although you will struggle to find parking lot because this place always crowded at lunch and dinner time :)
reviews.title: the best soto Banjar

reviews.text:
Good food. Good place.
Though a bit difficult to reach. Because this restaurant located a bit far for Samarinda.
reviews.title: Delicious

reviews.text:
This place is known for its Soto Banjar. They also have sate ayam. 
The soto is filled with chicken, potato cake, vermicelli, hard boiled egg and a few other ingredients. The broth gives you a home cooking feeling. 
You can have this soto either with nasi (rice) or ketupat (rice cake). 
A little moderate on price.
reviews.title: Early dinner

reviews.text: Soto Banjar Amado is one of traditional culinary that you can find in Kalimantan (Borneo). You can find not just Soto in this restourant. You can find also Sate Ayam (chicken satai). This restourant is one of my favorites resto.
reviews.title: The taste of traditional Borneo culinary

reviews.text: First time in Samarinda, my friend recommended this restaurant for lunch. And it taste so yummy. Even though a bit harder to get parking space, but the menu beat all the hassles. Hot soup with pieces of chicken and potato meatball, along with thick sauces will definitely relaxing your hard days. Add some lime and chili sauce to make perfect. For beverage, try ice kopyor or hot orange juice. Other dishes to try is chicken satay with peanut sauce. Price is reasonable. A must visit in Samarinda
reviews.title: Superb traditional hot chicken soup

reviews.text: the 'soto banjar' is famous for this resto. been there twice and still great taste. can't remember other foods in the menu.
reviews.title: great taste

reviews.text: Soto banjarnya rada beda dgn soto banjar ditempat lain. Kuahnya lebih berwarna dan gak segurih dr tempat lain
reviews.title: Soto banjar

reviews.text: soto banjar rasanya maknyus.suasana bersih dan nyaman.harganya terjangkau.cocok buat sarapan dan makan siang
reviews.title: Soto Banjar

reviews.text: Sekilas seperti soto lamongan, memiliki kuah kuning, irisan telur yang banyak, soun dan potongan daging ayam. Tapi ketika kuah ini dicampur dengan sambal, dibubuhi perasan jeruk dan sedikit kecap ( sesuai selera) terasa nikmat kesegarannya. Menu yang gak kalah enak dsni ada sate ayam. Beberapa menu lainnya juga disajikan disini seperti nasi goreng dan mie khas. Tapi yang paling membuat ketagihan adalah rasa teh nya yang unik.. enak.
reviews.title: Soto segar samarinda

reviews.text: Tempatnya sederhana dan soto disini enak..saat jam makan siang tmpt makan ini penuh dan sedikit panas..
reviews.title: Makan siang

reviews.text:
Hampir lima tahun di Samarinda, baru nyoba soto ini pas Agustus 2018. Itupun ga sengaja, karena pas ada kunjungan temen dinas dari Jakarta. Karena kondisi temen lg ga enak badan, jadilah makan yang berkuah. Sebelumnya uda pernah denger tentang ke hits an soto amado ini. Akhirnya aq beli dan bungkus tuk diaman d hotel.

Duh... ternyata rasanya emang enak..., kuahnya beda ama soto2 banjar yang pernah aq coba sebelumnya. Gurih en kaldunya terasa. Porsinya lumayan besar klo dibungkus, bisa buat berdua. sebenarnya ada sate ayam juga disana , tapi pas dateng uda abis, pdhl masi jam 7 malam. Kapan-kapan lah harus nyobain makan disanaaaa.....
reviews.title: Soto Banjar paling enaak di samarinda

reviews.text: Resto ini memang telah lama hadir melayani selera kuliner masyarakat kota Samarinda. Ada Soto, sate dan yang saya suka adalah mie gorengnya yang besar, merah dengan saos tomat dan potongan telur bebek dan irisan ayam, mirip sekali dengan mie bancir yang cukup ter kenal awalnya di kota tetangga Banjarmasin, namun dengan racikan bumbu Yang agak berbeda. Wajib dikunjungi bagi pecinta kuliner.
reviews.title: Mie nya mirip mie bancir

name: Raja Kepala Ikan
address: Jl. Awang Long no. 008, Samarinda 75242 Indonesia

reviews.text:
Went here for business dinner and the star is the Red Snapper Head Pallumara that cost only IDR 100k for 5 ons weight of the red snapper head; and it can be shared with 3-5 people 
Good food, good price 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
reviews.title: Best Pallumara!

reviews.text: Their gulai, woku or palumara is special, other cuisine also good, but the crab is terrible. Price is rather expensive.
reviews.title: Business Only

reviews.text: Great and delicious food. Taste of food is matched by the name Fish Head King. We ordered gropper fish and red snapper fish with coconut milk and pallumara (like a soup). Room is cozy and great for family or friends. Beverages is standart. Service little bit slow but no worry cause this is time for fastbreaking so many crowded when we ate there. Reccommended and we will back again.
reviews.title: Fastbreaking Together

reviews.text:
At a decent location and place, first after entering the main door, you need to choose the variety of seafood to cook. I choose a fish cooked as palumara, a kind of sour soup of fish. Get a plate of fried tempe or tofu for snack, and vegetables dishes.

It will take about 15 to 30 minutes for the meal to come. Be wise to choose appetizer such as the snack meal and decent drink while waiting the main course, so you will not starving during the wait. The meal are worth to wait. Enjoy!
reviews.title: Cozy Seafood Restaurant

photos.caption: The table, carved with Raja Kepala Ikan words

reviews.text: Excited, I find my favorite cuisine here, Palumara! Palumara is "red snapper fish head soup",  a heritage culinary from South Sulawesi. Love it!
reviews.title: Delicious Palumara!

reviews.text: Don't get deceived by it looks, this is not fancy restsurant by looks...but their rates for foods already are....so don't be surprised when you received the bill....food was fast to serve or maybe it was empty when we arrived....taste was okay but not spectacular..their specialty was fish...any kind would do just fine...
reviews.title: Surprisingly nice

reviews.text: salah satu menu andalan restoran ini adalah kepala kakap yang cukup lezat serta kerang saus tiram didukung dengan suasana yang mendukung untuk bersantap sehingga dapat direkomendasikan bagi wisatawan yang berkunjung di kota ini
reviews.title: Kepala kakap

reviews.text: Resto ini terletak di Samarinda,  Kalimantan Timur. Pada saat malam hari ramai,  masakan disini perpaduan antara makasar... Ada ikan bakar,  sup kepala ikan palunara,  sup kepala ikan asam pedas, brokoli cah bawang putih

reviews.text: Menu nya bervariasi. Rasanya enak dan harga pun ramah dikantong. Setiap saya kemari selalu bertemu dengan beberapa pengunjung WNA. Ini menandakan rasanya bersahabat dengan lidah mereka. Saya tidak memiliki menu favourite yang spesifik. Pelayanannya baik. Hanya untuk saran, buku menunya diperbaiki agar terlihat lebih berkelas.
reviews.title: Rasa mencukupi dan harga memadai

reviews.text: Rumah makan ini di tengah kota, parkiran yah lumayanlah, menunya sangat banyak, berbagai ikan ada. Mau makan di ruangan atau bisa pula beratap langit terbuka. soal harga tidak terlalu mahal kalau dibandingkan dengan rasa dan suasana

Tersedia menu seperti Sop kepala ikan, Udang saus raja, Ikan steam hongkong, Udang saus mentega, Ikan steam teriyaki, Udang asan manis, Sayur kailan cabe garam dan lainnya. reviews.text:
Firstly, they serve alot of different crabs, but they recommend the crabs asap, but for me. Its not really that great. However, the pari fish with sambal tery is the best one, the cooking is great and taste is really nice. Pricing is moderate for the fish, but the crabs kinda steep abit.
They also have a really big parking space. Thats why i give 4 star only. For the crabs.

reviews.title: The right place for Culinary experiences

reviews.text:
try the kepiting asap, and all kind of fish option

very fresh food, with reasonable price, location at city centre, easy to access
reviews.title: nice seafood

reviews.title: The best seafood in Samarinda

reviews.text:
One of my favorite restaurant in samarinda..
They served fresh seafood like crab, fish, squid, and also some vegetables..
Try kepiting asap "smoked crab", kepiting soka, kepiting telur asin "crab with salted egg", gosh that's such a foodgasm..
It's a bit pricey, but really worth it~

reviews.text: The best crab in town! 7 years ago I found this restaurant and every time I go to Samarinda I always eat this smoke crab. MUST TRY!
reviews.title: NO DOUBT!

reviews.text: Smoked crab dish here was soooo good! Crab meat was sweet, not overcooked, and the sauce was tasty. the fried fish rujak sauce and steam fish was also good. But, the main point of this restaurant was the smoked crab and its totally delicious! The best meal i’ve had in Samarinda i guess.
reviews.title: Seafood feast!!

reviews.text:
1st time here in samarinda and the seafood here mostly fresh. 
This rest served good crabs. I tried the saos padang crab and kepiting asap. I like the saos padang better than the asap crab.
The place is a bit hot as the weather in samarinda also very hot and no wind at all.
reviews.title: Crab

reviews.text:
Best smoked crab in town, pricey but yummy. Delicious ca pakis vegetable... Fish were good, we ordered the rojak fish. Clam was so so. Overall its a good place to dine but a bit pricey. 

The smoked crab can be ordered for take home. They wrap it nicely in a bag..
reviews.title: Yummyyyyy

reviews.text:
I had order the smoked crabs and crab eggs, crab fried rice and vegetable broccoli.
Crab in coat with seasonings such as rendang.
Crab fried rice was also good.
Very delicious.
Anyway must try all menus.
reviews.title: Smoked Crab in town 🦀

reviews.text: Went there and order kepiting asap (roasted crabs) and tofu and seaweed soup. All taste great and fresh. value for money and pretty quick service.
reviews.title: fresh seafood, taste great !

reviews.text:
I only here to company my friend for their famous smoke crab. So I thought the fist will be just okey, but turns out it was one of the best dish i ever try.

It was fried senangin fish with rujak dressing.
The fried fish is crispy and the rujak dressing will give you sweet and sour taste. The dressing also have big chunk of peanuts, pineapple and cucumber.
reviews.title: Fried fish with rujak dressing

reviews.text: I dont really like crab but when i accompanied my mate who is really enjoying his dish i was interested to try. Then guest what..i ate almost all of the crabs on the server plate :)). I suggest dont visit in the public holiday or you will wait so long because it's much crowded.
reviews.title: Best smoked crab ever

reviews.text:
The restaurant was fulled. I had been waiting for almost 1 hour when finally the dishes were ready.
The food was delicious. Reasonable price. Price +- 300k rupiah for 3 people.
How to get there? It is located on Abul Hasan Street. If u alone , better u go there by gojek. The Taxi price was costly. We had to pay 50k rupiah for only 10 minute trip.
reviews.title: Tempting crab

reviews.text:
Their smoked crab is awesome, smoky and still smooth, not dry. should try this when in samarinda. in short vacation if my friend want to go to samarinda and i can go too i will eat lunch or dinner in this restaurant.. not to expensive too.

two thumbs up..
reviews.title: 1st time ever try smoked crab

reviews.text: They served best smoked-crab ever, worth every penny. You should eat in this place when you're in Samarinda!
reviews.title: A heaven for sea food lovers! (Surga seafood di timur kalimantan!)

reviews.text: their signature dish smoked crab is amazing and you have to try it when visit this resto. but it's locate at Abul Hasan Street in Samarinda and sometimes it's quite hard to find parking lot. avoid peak hours.
reviews.title: smoked crab

reviews.text: I went here since myfriend recommended this place. It is renowned for its smoked crab. So, that's what I ordered. The portion is big enough, so you can share it with 2-4 friends. The crab is originally good, they serve female crabs full of crab meat and crab eggs in it. But it is so covered with seasoning and ingredients you could hardly taste the crab. Don't imagine that you could enjoy food in a nice restaurant here, it is hot and full of smoke from the crab burning area and needs to pay more attention to its cleanliness. Anyhow, just try it but don't expect too much.
reviews.title: a famous eatery which needs upgrade

address: Jl. Bukit Barisan no. 01 Kawasan Terpadu Alaya, Samarinda 75122 Indonesia

reviews.text: Located in the Hill of Alaya, North side of Samarinda City the capital city of Kalimantan Timur, Indonesia. Recommended for hangout in the weekend for dinner and spend your night with just chat and coffee party.
reviews.title: Alaya Food Festival, the Hill of Alaya

reviews.text: Open only on afternoon until night. Have many variety of food, mostly taste good. Price is avarage for food court.
reviews.title: Variety of food

reviews.text: Nice place, many foods you can try it there such as Japanese, Indonesian foods like soto banjar, satay and fried rice, dessert and many more you should try it
reviews.title: Good place and many foods there

reviews.text: This place is very busy during weekend for dinner and the location near the down town but little bit difficult to find the car park during weekend.food and beverage many choices for the menu,some places have live music as well.
reviews.title: Many choices for dinner in Samarinda

reviews.text:
Pros: 
The tenants are famous for the locals. 
Various of food choices. 
Free parking lot, which is very rare in the town
Reasonable price

cons:
the payment method is very primitive. only accept cash and we have to queue twice, firstly at the tenant when ordering food, secondly at the cashier to pay the bill, which is not practical when it is crowded. i felt frustrated when it happened. they must consider using prepaid card for more pratical use. I do not want to go there in the weekend.

the waitresses or the tenants are lazy to deliver the food if we sit too far from them. that time i ordered Sabindo, i had to collect the food i ordered at the tenant, it made me queue 3 times just to have the food and teh tarik there. I will never order at Sabindo anymore.

suggestion: you must provide small change money, because the cashier seldom give you the change money
reviews.title: Nice Outdoor Hangout Place

reviews.text: Sering banget ke food fest alaya karena deket banget dari rumah, rasa makanannya lumayan tapi harganya emang agak sedikit diatas harga normal. Pembayarannya juga lumayan ribet karena harus bolak balik tenant ke kasir balik ke tenant lagi karena kasir semua penjual jadi satu.

reviews.text: Tempat makan ini lokasinya persis di tengah perumahan. perumahannya besar dan lengkap, ada juga jajaran ruko, praktek dokter, bank, pusat perbelanjaan dll. Mau makan berat ataupun ringan lengkap. mau nongkrong, ngopi-ngopi sampai tengah malam juga Ok aja. setiap akhir pekan, sabtu dan minggu biasanya area ini hingar bingar oleh suara musik dadakan. jadi bagi yang gak suka dengar musik keras jangan kesini waktu akhir pekan, atau bisa juga pilih lokasi yang agak ke ujung, jadi gak begitu bising. kelemahannya adalah kalau mau sholat. hanya tersedia musholla kecil, dan sering kotor.
reviews.title: Tempat Makan dan nongkorng di Tengah kompleks perumahan

reviews.text: Tempat yang asyik dan tepat  buat berkumpul bareng ( keluarga, teman)  santai mau pun buat urusan, karena tempat ini lokasinya yang presentatif dan recomended. reviews.text:
Karena kemarin di Samarinda, malamnya saya berdua sempat makan di Ong Palace.

Restorannya sih besar. Ramah disabilitas. Namun, saat masuk terdapat aroma restoran yang kurang sedap, walaupun sesaat saja.

Dan, begitu saya melihat menunya, saya agak terkejut. Mahal - mahal! Ayamnya seekor 250 ribuan, udangnya 130 ribuan. Begitupun belum termasuk tax & servis 15.5 persen. Yang bahkan, ayamnya lebih mahal daripada ayam di Jakarta.

Ayam goreng khas mereka juga menurut saya kurang gurih untuk seharga segitu. Lebih menyenangkan udang gandumnya.

Dengan harga begitu apakah Ong Palace layak dikunjungi? Saya rasa kurang begitu menarik. Harganya hanya bisa membuat kantong bolong.

Namun, memang mereka juga terlihat ada menu steamboat, karena diletakannya kompor kecil di beberapa meja.

Mungkin karena peruntukkan awal dari restoran ini adalah restoran keluarga, ya.

"Roti Durian" it's like indonesian sweet bread filled with durian jam. The bread itself is sweet and the durian jam also sweet (i think they added more sugar in the jam) so makes this bread very sweet, not suit with my taste. If you love sweet and strong smell , this will be your next big thing

name: Kedai Sabindo
address: Jl. Letjend R.Soeprapto no. 5D, Samarinda 75123 Indonesia

reviews.text:
This place is good for hangout with friends..
They served malay and some of india's food..
If you go in weekend night, sometimes you can't get a seat because many people will eat here..
You should order roti tisu milo, roti cane kari, jus sirsak, or teh tarik (my friend said its good), worth to try..
reviews.title: Worth to try

reviews.text: Saya selalu menyempatkan makan di sini kalau sedang mudik ke Samarinda. Menu favorit saya adalah wan tan ho dan es teh tarik. Pelayanannya cepat. Menunya mulai dari makanan ringan (roti tissue, canai), beberapa jenis mie dan makanan berat ala Malaysia/Singapore. Minuman juga ada banyak pilihan. Harga pun masih terjangkau. Pada jam makan malam tempat ini selalu ramai. Bagi yang membawa mobil kadang agak sulit untuk parkir, tapi ada tukang parkir yang bisa membantu. Btw, jangan salah minum air dari teko kecil berwarna emas yang ada di tiap meja karena itu air untuk cuci tangan :D .

reviews.text: Menu nya beragam, dari makanan ringan hingga beratpun ada. Makanan nya enak enak apalagi kuah karenya. roti tisunya pun juara lah. tempat nya luas harga makanannya pun ternjangkau
reviews.title: Makan Lezat dengan Harga yang Terjangkau

reviews.text: Tempat nya ditengah kota dan di pinggir jalan besar makananx enak pelayanannya juga ramah recommended deh
reviews.title: Makan

reviews.text: saya biasanya menjadikan tempat ini alternatif jika sedang kangen makanan malaya. harganya normally untuk rasa yang di tawarkan. pesan roti tissue lebih dulu untuk camilan sambil menunggu pesanan yang lain di buatkan. Teh tarik nya lumayan dan yang jelas tempatnya cukup mudah di datangi.

reviews.text: Suka sekali sama teh tarik dan roti canai dengan kuah kare. menunya jarang ditemui di tempat lain. canai nya enak banget. Tempatnya enak buat nongkrong dan makanannya enak dan harga nya terjangkau.

reviews.text: Kedai Sabindo ada dua. Cabang satunya lagi di Alaya food festival. Menu yang ada di sini dengan yang ada di Alaya sama saja. Tetapi jam bukanya berbeda, untuk yang di Alaya, bukanya jam 5 pm sampai jam 11pm. Di sini, bukanya dari jam 10 am kalau tidak salah. Rasa memang tidak perlu diragukan lagi, enak! Karinya cocok dengan selera saya. Menu favorit kita adalah roti canai dengan kari daging dan roti tisu milo cheese. Minumannya neslo ice (nescafe milo) dan es teh tarik. Di kedai Sabindo ini bisa juga untuk makan siang. Apabila ingin nongkrong dengan teman atau keluarga, saya sarankan makan di Alaya saja. Tempat lebih luas dan suasananya lebih asik serta parkir yang lebih luas. Foto yang saya lampirkan adalah tenant sabindo yang ada di Alaya

reviews.text: Tempat makan yg menyediakan makanan2 khas malaysia, enak dan lokasi tepat di daerah macet hehe. Wajib coba roti tisu, teh tarik dan mie susu nya ketika ke sini, haucek. Tempatnya jg cocok buat bukber atau nongki rame2

reviews.text: Baru buka di sore hari aja udah langsung rame banget, bahkan walaupun bukan weekend. Suasanya lumayan nyaman buat ngobrol2 sambil nunggu makanan yang dipesan -yg mana disiapinnya rada lama emang-. Kalo mau kesini, jangan dalam keadaan laper banget, ntar bawaannya emosi loh hahaha. Tapi emang rasa makanannya worth it banget dgn lamanya nunggu. Roti tissuenya enaaak sekali dan favorit saya yg lain selain itu adalah mie goren spesialnya dan es lidah buayanya. reviews.text:
Sambil menikmati suasana malam di Samarinda juga menyantap kuliner yang sangat variatif di sekitar Alaya.
Musik jazz yg dimainkan oleh local band dan suasana yg cozy membuat betah berlama-lama disini.

Akhirnya pilihan jatuh pada roti cobra dan lemon sui peng untuk minumannya.

Roti cobra nya unik dan menarik. Perpaduan roti cane, kari ayam, kari daging dan telor mata sapi.

Cane nya renyah dan empuk, bumbu kari nya sangat terasa. Ditambah lagi dengan daging yg lembut serta dilengkapi dengan telur mata sapi membuat perpaduan ini menjadi serasi.

Lemon Sui Peng (air lemon) nya segar, sayangnya agak kebanyakan gula.

Tapi agak lama juga menunggu makanannya.

reviews.text:
Saya bersama keluarga beberapa kali mengunjungi tempat makan ini. Sabindo menyediakan beberapa jenis makanan seperti nasi goreng dengan beragam varian, mie, dan beberapa jenis camilan lainnya seperti roti tisu, canai, dan lain-lain.
Favorit saya setiap mengunjungi Sabindo adalah roti tisunya, dengan pilihan varian roti tisu milo, roti tisu susu, atau roti susu keju.
Sayangnya, Sabindo tidak menyediakan area bebas rokok sehingga saya merasa agak terganggu ketika harus duduk berdampingan meja dengan pengunjung yang merokok. Bangunan juga terasa kurang nyaman karena tidak begitu luas sehingga pengunjung yang datang pada waktu ramai harus duduk di luar ruangan yang berada persis di pinggir jalan raya.
Saya lebih memilih untuk membawa pulang makanan pesanan saya (take away) daripada makan sambil menghirup debu jalan atau kendaraan yang lalu lalang.
reviews.title: Roti Tisu Favorit!

reviews.text:
This is the first Torani restaurant in Samarinda. Smaller than the other store but packed the same taste.
We came here on one hot sunny day for lunch.
Fish dishes were the flavor of the day. So, we ordered a steamed grouper and red snapper palumara (Makassar specialty dish).
The steamed grouper was exquisite, tender and the sauce complimented the fish nicely.
Palumara was my personal favorite, very vibrant. Hot, spicy, sour...all in one.
So, if you're ever in Samarinda, pay this place a visit.
reviews.title: Fish lunch in Samarinda

name: Lezat Baru Restaurant
address: Jl Mulawarman, Samarinda 75112 Indonesia

reviews.text:
My dad first went to Samarinda more than 30 years ago and this restaurant has become a fixture of city's Chinese food then. Everytime this restaurant's name comes up, he always remembers the Oyster in Butter Sauce dishes that he had there. He says that the oysters were big in size and tasted fresh and juicy. 
Following the story of my dad I went to this restaurant several years ago, and it becomes my favorite. Not for oysters, but for Cap Cay Goreng (Fried Mixed Vegetable) and Fried Pork. 
I would recommend this restaurant to anyone who wants to try the Chinese food taste of Samarinda. Recently, many Chinese food restaurant opened in this city, but cooked by chefs from Pontianak. So these new restaurants do not offer the classic taste of Samarinda. 
If you happen to be in Samarinda, you can find Lezat Baru within short walking distance from Swissbel Hotel Borneo. When you're there, hopefully you can still meet a waiter who has worked in the restaurant for ages. He's a legend.
reviews.title: Samarinda's Chinese Food Classic Restaurant

reviews.text: They are one of the oldest chinese restaurant in Samarinda.. The taste quite good .. Their fried chicken is good also their sweet fried pork. But beware samarinda chinese usually charge a lot for the food price..

The food is super nice, i really recommend to go for their "saos mentega" which is really good, although it made me feel really guilty. The place is air conditioned, quite nice. The price though, as one of the classics, it is not cheap, but i can assure the taste will offset the price.

Restoran chinese banyak sekali di samarinda, dan lezat baru adalah salah satu yang tergolong klasik di samarinda. Makanannya super enak, apalagi saus mentega mereka, walaupun agak berdosa rasanya makan itu. harganya.. tidak murah, namun saya bisa menjamin bahwa rasa makannya worth it 1 harganya

As other family run restaurant don't expect great service like a fancy restaurant at hotel but the ambiance there is cozy and quiet peaceful.
Everytime I go there always see many business people from coal mining company chatting and sharing information. (Probably a good head start for those who want to do mining business in Samarinda; even the owner I believe has some business channels as well)

reviews.text:
This place is talk of the town when in comes to crab. It's been around for years and the restaurant have transformed to a more modern look, but the taste remained the same.
Ordered a portion of boiled crab (no sauce). A portion is a crab and a half.
The spices used for boiling enhanced the crab's taste. Served with a chilly, peanut paste and pineapple paste. Amazing stuff.
A must try while you're in Samarinda

reviews.text:
I had a very memorable experienced eating here, the good place for seafood lover especially crab maniac. Ordered crab (female) with sari bhoga sauce which was amazingly delicious, jumbo, and meaty. Other dish was grilled iridescent shark (ikan patin bakar) also in a giant size, the fried squid was so crunchy and jumbo as well. I don't know why the size here were all big which make this restaurant suitable for family or friends in big group. Their sayur asam also fresh and citrusy. 

It is a casual and modest dining place, no AC inside, but there is a parking lot in front of the restaurant. This place is not too big, and if you or your friend know the owner, might want to check before heading because the crab sold out fast. When visiting this town, make sure to try this place. Awesome!

reviews.text: We do not expect to find a sundanese resto as a favourite place in Samarinda. Saung Pasundan means "Sundanese (western Javanese) House", is crowded by guests appreciating the food from across the sea. The design of the place is typically sundanese. Long tables lined up to serve sundanese food, mostly prepared food. From steamed mushroom/chicken/egg in banana leaves (pepes), fried chickens, stir fried beef, tamarind vegs soup (sayur asam), various chili paste/sauce, clear spinach soup (sayur bening), coconut gravy vegs soup (lodeh) and papadam (kerupuk). As a guest coming from the homeland of sundanese, I have to tell that the taste is not authentic sundanese. I can feel strange flavor and alien herbs in my mouth, a native of sunda mouth. However, the overall food quality is good and tasty. Besides, who cares in Samarinda for a proper pepes and sambal dadak taste.
reviews.title: Western Java food in Samarinda
